Bug 2054872 - Avoid unwanted scroll on message delete and new mail arrival. r=mkmelin

After operations that change the message view (deleting a message,
new mail replacing a thread root, or delete completing in search
views), RestoreSelection could silently fail because the preserved
key was removed from m_keys. This left the selection empty, causing
mJSTree->Invalidate() to trigger scrollToLatestRowIfNoSelection()
in the JS tree shim, which scrolled the view away from the user's
position.

Fix by using InvalidateRange(0, GetSize() - 1) instead of
Invalidate() in three cleanup paths where the scroll behavior is
undesirable:

- nsMsgThreadedDBView::OnNewHeader
- nsMsgThreadedDBView::RemoveByIndex
- nsMsgSearchDBView::OnDeleteCompleted

InvalidateRange repaints existing rows in-place without destroying
the DOM or triggering a scroll reset, and is also cheaper since it
reuses existing row elements rather than rebuilding the entire
buffer from scratch.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D312233

diff --git a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
--- a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
+++ b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgSearchDBView.cpp
@@ -1391,8 +1391,8 @@ nsMsgSearchDBView::OnDeleteCompleted(boo
       // This seems to be the easiest way to update the row count of the
       // XUL tree and invalidate it.
       mTree->EndUpdateBatch();
     }
-    if (mJSTree) mJSTree->Invalidate();
+    if (mJSTree) mJSTree->InvalidateRange(0, GetSize() - 1);
   }
   return NS_OK;
 }
diff --git a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgThreadedDBView.cpp b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgThreadedDBView.cpp
--- a/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgThreadedDBView.cpp
+++ b/mailnews/base/src/nsMsgThreadedDBView.cpp
@@ -592,9 +592,9 @@ nsresult nsMsgThreadedDBView::OnNewHeade
       if (mTree) {
         mTree->Invalidate();
       }
       if (mJSTree) {
-        mJSTree->Invalidate();
+        mJSTree->InvalidateRange(0, GetSize() - 1);
       }
     }
   });
 
@@ -719,9 +719,9 @@ nsresult nsMsgThreadedDBView::RemoveByIn
         if (mTree) {
           mTree->Invalidate();
         }
         if (mJSTree) {
-          mJSTree->Invalidate();
+          mJSTree->InvalidateRange(0, GetSize() - 1);
